<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Marax"><i>Click here for full details on the marax</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Marsupial Devil"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Marsupial Devil</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 180</i></a><br />This toothy marsupial has a perhaps undeserved reputation for ferocity.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Marsupial Devil"><i>Click here for full details on the marsupial devil</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Marsupial Lion"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Marsupial Lion</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 180</i></a><br />Somewhat slimmer than the standard lion, the marsupial lion is no less dangerous in battle.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Marsupial Lion"><i>Click here for full details on the marsupial lion</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Megafauna (Archelon)">Megafauna (Archelon)</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8odu?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary-3" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Bestiary 3 pg. 311</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Archelon"><i>Link</i></a><br />The shell of this immense sea turtle easily spans 12 feet in length. Its narrow head ends in a hooked beak.
