" target="_blank"><i>Animal Archive pg. 29</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Moose"><i>Link</i></a><br />Powerful and often ill tempered, the moose is an intimidating choice for an animal companion.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Moose"><i>Click here for full details on the moose</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Moray Eel"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Moray Eel</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8auu?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder RPG Bestiary pg. 119</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Giant Moray Eel"><i>Link</i></a><br />This sixteen-foot-long eel slithers through the water with uncanny grace, mouth open to display large teeth and a second set of jaws.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Moray Eel"><i>Click here for full details on the moray eel</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Mosquito, Giant"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Mosquito, Giant</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 185</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Giant Mosquito"><i>Link</i></a><br />Between its bloodthirsty nature and the annoying drone of its wings, the giant mosquito is a much-loathed creature. Unlike its smaller cousins, a giant mosquito can easily kill larger creatures by draining them of their blood.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Mosquito, Giant"><i>Click here for full details on the mosquito, giant</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Narwhale"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Narwhale</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9g9x?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary-5
" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Bestiary 5 pg. 313</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Narwhal"><i>Link</i></a><br />This small whale lacks a dorsal fin and has pale, mottled skin, but its most notable feature is the single tusk protruding from its nose, easily as long as a human.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Narwhale"><i>Click here for full details on the narwhale</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Octopus"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Octopus</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8auu?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder RPG Bestiary pg. 219</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Octopus"><i>Link</i></a><br />Eight tentacles, each adorned with rows of countless suckers, unfurl from the barrel-shaped body of this large-eyed creature.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Octopus"><i>Click here for full details on the octopus</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Orca"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Orca</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8auu?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder RPG Bestiary pg. 88</i></a><br />This sleek black whale has a distinctive white patch near each eye and a mouth filled with sharp teeth.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Orca"><i>Click here for full details on the orca</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ornithomimosaur"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Ornithomimosaur</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 180</i></a><br />This bipedal dinosaur has long legs built for speed and a long neck that gives it an ostrichlike profile.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ornithomimosaur"><i>Click here for full details on the ornithomimosaur</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ostrich"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Ostrich</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy93n8?Pathfinder-Campaign-Setting-Osirion-Legacy-of-Pharaohs" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Osirion, Legacy of the Pharaohs pg. 55</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Ostrich"><i>Link</i></a><br />This human-sized bird has a long neck and legs sprouting from a round body covered in fluffy gray feathers.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ostrich"><i>Click here for full details on the ostrich</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Owl, Giant"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Owl, Giant</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 181</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Giant Owl"><i>Link</i></a><br />Unlike the magical beast of the same name, this owl is a mundane but unusually large specimen of its kind, with powerful wings and deadly talons.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Owl, Giant"><i>Click here for full details on the owl, giant</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Panda"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Panda</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 181</i></a>, <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8w7p?Pathfinder-Player-Companion-Animal-Archive
