<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pilo"><i>Click here for full details on the pilo</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Plesiosaurus"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Plesiosaurus</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9g9x?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary-5
" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Bestiary 5 pg. 313</i></a><br />This streamlined reptile has a long, serpentine neck, at the end of which glares a many-fanged head.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Plesiosaurus"><i>Click here for full details on the plesiosaurus</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Polar Bear">Polar Bear</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9g9x?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary-5
" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Bestiary 5 pg. 313</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Polar Bear"><i>Link</i></a><br />Red gore stains this bear’s muzzle, creating a striking contrast against its white fur.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Polar Bear"><i>Click here for full details on the polar bear</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pony"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Pony</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/pathfinderRPG/v5748btpy88yj" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>PRPG Core Rulebook pg. 54</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Pony"><i>Link</i></a><br />This squat equine plods forward with large, curious eyes. As it nears, it extends its muzzle, clearly expecting a treat.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pony"><i>Click here for full details on the pony</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Porcupine, Giant"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Porcupine, Giant</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 181</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Giant Porcupine"><i>Link</i></a><br />This lumbering forest creature is adorned with an array of long, sharp quills that protrude from its coarse pelt.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Porcupine, Giant"><i>Click here for full details on the porcupine, giant</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Prionosuchus"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Prionosuchus</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 181</i></a><br />This primeval crocodile is equally effective in the water and on land. Its jaws are capable of crushing things with great force.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Prionosuchus"><i>Click here for full details on the prionosuchus</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pterosaur (Dimorphodon)"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Pterosaur (Dimorphodon)</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/pathfinder/adventurePath/theSerpentsSkull/v5748btpy8b7v" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder #37: Souls for Smuggler's Shiv pg. 83</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Dimorphodon"><i>Link</i></a><br />The head of this colorful red and purple flying reptile is overly large, and its jaws are lined with tiny sharp teeth.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pterosaur (Dimorphodon)"><i>Click here for full details on the pterosaur (dimorphodon)</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pterosaur (Quetzalcoatlus)"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Pterosaur (Quetzalcoatlus)</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/pathfinder/adventurePath/theSerpentsSkull/v5748btpy8b7v" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder #37: Souls for Smuggler's Shiv pg. 83</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Quetzalcoatlus"><i>Link</i></a><br />This immense flying reptile has a staggering wingspan and a brightly colored head with a razor-sharp beak.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pterosaur (Quetzalcoatlus)"><i>Click here for full details on the pterosaur (quetzalcoatlus)</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Pygmy Hippopotamus"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Pygmy Hippopotamus</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/store/downloads/pathfinder/pathfinderChronicles/pathfinderRPG/v5748btpy8evh" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Heart of the Jungle pg. 60</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Hippopotamus"><i>Link</i></a><br />This fleshy behemoth wallows forward on four stumpy legs. Its jaws spread wide in a roar of challenge, exposing massive, tusk-like teeth.
