<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Quetzalcoatlus"><i>Click here for full details on the quetzalcoatlus</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ram"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Ram</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/pathfinderRPG/v5748btpy8hif" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Bestiary 2 pg. 154</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Ram"><i>Link</i></a><br />A formidable pair of heavy horns curls from the forehead of this sturdy, brown-and-white-furred ram.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ram"><i>Click here for full details on the ram</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Rash Creeper"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif" title="Plant companions are available only as allowed by specific archetypes or other options." style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Rash Creeper</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 183</i></a><br />This mass of creeping vines and leaves slithers almost like a snake. Contact with this predatory plant causes a sickening and sometimes debilitating rash.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Rash Creeper"><i>Click here for full details on the rash creeper</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Raven, Giant"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Raven, Giant</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9g0q?Pathfinder-Adventure-Path-97-In-Hells-Bright-Shadow
