<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Raven, Giant"><i>Click here for full details on the raven, giant</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Reef Snake"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Reef Snake</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 181</i></a><br />Highly venomous and an excellent swimmer, the brightly colored reef snake is at home in tidal waters but can slither about on land if needed.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Reef Snake"><i>Click here for full details on the reef snake</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Reindeer"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Reindeer</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9ujo" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Wilderness pg. 181</i></a><br />A denizen of the frozen tundra, the reindeer is a sure-footed companion in icy terrain, and it can used for transportation as well as defense.<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Reindeer"><i>Click here for full details on the reindeer</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Rhinoceros"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Rhinoceros</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8auu?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Bestiary" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder RPG Bestiary pg. 235</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Rhinoceros"><i>Link</i></a><br />This rhinoceros has a low-slung head with twisted ears that lie back along its neck.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Rhinoceros"><i>Click here for full details on the rhinoceros</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Riding Python">Riding Python</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9926?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Monster-Codex
" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Monster Codex pg. 128</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Venomous Snake"><i>Link</i></a><br />This brightly colored snake assumes an aggressive posture, its hissing mouth open to display its fangs.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Riding Python"><i>Click here for full details on the riding python</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Riding Rat"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbolN.gif" title="Legal only for Ratfolk PCs" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Riding Rat</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9926?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Monster-Codex
" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Monster Codex pg. 177</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Dire Rat"><i>Link</i></a><br />This filthy rat is the size of a small dog. It has a coat of coarse fur, a long and scabby tail, and two glittering eyes.
<br /><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Riding Rat"><i>Click here for full details on the riding rat</i></a>.<br /><br /><h2 class="title"><a href="DruidCompanions.aspx?ItemName=Ringhorn"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Ringhorn</a></h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy9npj" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Pathfinder #115: Trail of the Hunted pg. 83</i></a><br /><b>Monster Entry</b> <a href="MonsterDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Ringhorn"><i>Link</i></a><br />The horns of this goatlike deer grow up and curve around into a pair of massive, spiraling rings atop its head.
